    "plan_content": "Here's my complete implementation plan for the Stepper compound component:\n\n---\n\n## What I found in the codebase\n\nThe key reference is **`carousel.tsx`** — the only existing component that builds its own React context from scratch (rather than wrapping Radix UI). The Stepper will follow the same dual-context pattern.\n\nOther conventions confirmed:\n- `\"use client\"` + function declarations throughout\n- `data-slot=\"...\"` on every rendered element\n- `React.ComponentProps<\"element\">` for all prop types\n- `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for class merging\n- Named exports in UI components, default exports in demo files\n\n---\n\n## Plan (4 Steps)\n\n**Step 1 — `ui/stepper.tsx`** (new file)\n\nTwo private React contexts + hooks:\n- **`StepperContext`**: `{ activeStep, orientation }` — provided by `Stepper`, consumed by `StepperSeparator`, `StepperContent`\n- **`StepperItemContext`**: `{ step, state }` — provided by `StepperItem`, consumed by `StepperTrigger` and `StepperSeparator`\n\nThe `state` is computed as: `step < activeStep → \"completed\"`, `step === activeStep → \"active\"`, else `\"pending\"`.\n\n| Component | Element | Key behavior |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Stepper` | `<div>` | Root provider; `flex-row items-center` or `flex-col` |\n| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | Per-step provider; sets `data-state`, `data-step` |\n| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | Rounded circle; shows step number or children; color-coded by state |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | `text-sm font-medium` |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | `text-sm text-muted-foreground` |\n| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | `flex-1 h-px`; `bg-primary` when item is `\"completed\"`, else `bg-border` |\n| `StepperContent` | `<div>` | Returns `null` when `step !== activeStep` |\n\n**Step 2 — `examples/stepper-demo.tsx`** (new file)\n\n3-step horizontal stepper (Account → Profile → Complete) with `React.useState(1)` for active step, `StepperContent` panels for each step, and Next/Previous buttons disabled at boundaries.\n\n**Step 3 — `ui/_registry.ts`** (insert only)\n\nAdd `\"stepper\"` entry after the `spinner` entry (line 563), before `switch`. No external `dependencies` — pure React + Tailwind.\n\n**Step 4 — `examples/_registry.ts`** (insert only)\n\nAdd `\"stepper-demo\"` entry after `spinner-item` (line 2124), before `switch-demo`, with `registryDependencies: [\"stepper\"]`.",
